Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}.

Pop the radishes into a #small bowl{}. Add the @rice vinegar{15%g}, a
drizzle of @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @sugar{}.

Mix together and set aside to pickle.

Sandwich each @British pork loin steaks{2} between two pieces of
#baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a
bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1cm thick. Season with @salt{}
and @black pepper{}.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} and @black sesame seeds{5%g} into another
#medium bowl{}, then season with @salt for the breadcrumbs{1/2%tsp} and
@black pepper{}.

Dip the pork into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Transfer to a #plate{}. Important: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw meat and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely
coat the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the pork fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins
> before you add the pork.

Once hot, carefully lay the pork into the frying pan, reduce the heat to
medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}
total. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the pork to a plate lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Discard the oil from the pork frying pan and wipe clean. Return to medium-high
heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @gochujang paste{30%g}, @honey{15%g} and @water{50%ml}.
Cook until the sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir through the @butter{20%g} until melted.

When everything's ready, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} with the pickled radish.

Share the pork schnitzel between your plates, then serve your fries and salad
alongside.

Drizzle over the honey-gochujang butter sauce to finish.

Enjoy!